PS\: Darn developers, follow Naming Conventions! 
Naming conventions are a set of guidelines that developers follow to write clear and readable code. 
Following widely accepted conventions ensures that your code can be easily understood by other developers familiar with Java. 
Use camelCase for your variables like myMagicWand (lowercase first letter, capitalize subsequent words, no spaces between) 
So we can read your code easily, or I'll turn you all into newts!!! 
Consistent naming makes it easier for developers to read and understand code. 
Clear, descriptive names reduce confusion about what a class, method, or variable does.
